--- README.md ---
   250	
   251	If a migration fails mid-execution, the version is marked dirty. Fix the issue, then run `migrate set` to clear the dirty flag before retrying.
   252	
   253	### `generate` -- Go Code Generation
   254	
   255	Generates type-safe Go structs with Spanner column tags, CRUD mutation methods
   256	(`Insert`, `Update`, `InsertOrUpdate`, `Delete`), commit timestamp-aware helper
   257	methods, and `FindByPrimaryKey` functions.
   258	
   259	```console
   260	# Generate from a live database
   261	spanner-manager generate -o ./models -p my-project -i my-instance -d my-db
   262	
   263	# Generate from a DDL file (no database connection needed)
   264	spanner-manager generate --from-ddl schema.sql -o ./models
   265	
   266	# Full example with all options
   267	spanner-manager generate --from-ddl schema.sql -o ./models \
   268	  --package models \
   269	  --tables Runs,Projects \
   270	  --singularize-rows \
   271	  --row-suffix Row \
   272	  --suffix .gen.go \
   273	  --ignore-tables SchemaMigrations \
   274	  --config codegen.yaml
   275	```
   276	
   277	Generation writes a shared `spanner_db` helper and one file per table into the output directory. The `header.go.tmpl` template is used as the header section of each generated file rather than producing a standalone `spanner_header` file. This is useful when you want generated models checked into the repository.
   278	
   279	| Flag | Description |
